value.title: Column: White House of Horrors: A Halloween-themed poem about Donald Trump
value.excerpt: The latest TrumPoem, a rhyming account of the presidency of Donald J. Trump, loosely based on his words and acts.

value.title: Pence highlights economic recovery report at Nevada rally
value.excerpt: RENO, Nev. (AP) — Vice President Mike Pence urged early in-person voting and highlighted reports of a partial economic recovery during a rally Thursday in Reno, hoping to drum up enthusiasm in Nevada in the final days before the election.

value.title: Facebook admits it 'improperly' blocked some political ads due to 'technical issues' as Joe Biden's campaign slams it for being 'wholly unprepared'
value.excerpt: Facebook said no ads were blocked "because of any partisan consideration," as Biden's camp accused the company of offering "no clarity" on the issue.

value.title: ‘People Are Going To Be Shocked’: Return of the ‘Shy’ Trump Voter?
value.excerpt: In 2016, pollsters Arie Kapteyn and Robert Cahaly saw Trump coming. In 2020, they see polls again underestimating his support.

value.title: Kamala Harris Says Political Figures Mispronouncing Her Name Are "Predictable and Childish"
value.excerpt: Kamala Harris joined Trevor Noah on The Daily Social Distancing Show Thursday night where she addressed those who mispronounce her name. "Why does it seem like it becomes harder to pronounce your name the more conservative a person is?

value.title: Lil Wayne reveals 'great meeting' with Trump, prompting Twitter users to respond
value.excerpt: Lil Wayne made a big splash on Twitter after he revealed that he met with Trump, sharing a friendly photo the two of them took together.

value.title: Sean Hannity: Biden depicting ‘scary’ image of America despite surging economy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is making America out to be a country besieged by doom and gloom with five days left until the election, but “Hannity” host Sean Hannity argued Thursday the nation is actually on an upswing.

value.title: Trump meets with Army unit that conducted Al-Baghdadi raid, awards citation
value.excerpt: President Trump has awarded a citation to the Army special operations unit that conducted the 2019 raid resulting in the death of notorious Islamic State leader Abu Bakr Al-Baghdadi.

value.title: Kudlow: Biden's economic plan would crush middle class, cost millions of jobs over next decade
value.excerpt: A Joe Biden presidency would cripple the U.S. economy and cause the loss of an estimated five million American jobs by 2030, White House economic adviser Larry Kudlow told "The Ingraham Angle" on Thursday.

value.title: Schumer calls Trump 'a moron' over coronavirus response
value.excerpt: Senate Minority Leader Charles Schumer (D-N.Y.) on Thursday said the federal government is failing to react appropriately to surging coronavirus cases around the country because President Trump is “a moron.

value.title: Trump's disrespect of Sen. Martha McSally was painful to watch
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump treated Sen. Martha McSally like a second-class citizen during his Goodyear rally. That's the thanks she gets, for her loyalty.

value.title: 'West Wing' star Martin Sheen: Donald Trump gets away with more than any TV president could
value.excerpt: West Wing' is my escape from the Trump era. Its TV public servants know what the right thing is and they're on speaking terms with their better angels.

value.title: Trump is touting the record-shattering GDP report as evidence of a full economic rebound. Here's why the recovery actually has much further to go.
value.excerpt: The US economy grew 7.4% in Q3, or 33.1% at an annualized rate. Many economists say growth is slowing down without another stimulus package.

value.title: Glenn Greenwald leaves The Intercept, claiming he was ‘censored’ over an article he wrote on Joe Biden
value.excerpt: Journalist Glenn Greenwald said Thursday that he was leaving The Intercept, the news website he helped found, claiming that it had refused to publish an article he wrote on Joe Biden unless he removed sections that were critical of the Democratic presidential nominee.

value.title: Retired Minnesota police officers asked to be Trump poll watchers in 'rough neighborhoods'
value.excerpt: A volunteer attorney for the Trump 2020 campaign is seeking retired officers to work as poll challengers in Minnesota.

value.title: Former Michigan Gov. Rick Snyder on being a 'proud Republican' who voted for Biden
value.excerpt: Snyder served eight years as governor and was replaced by Democrat Gretchen Whitmer in 2019.

value.title: Chuck Todd Slammed For Saying Joe Biden Takes COVID-19 'Too Seriously'
value.excerpt: The MSNBC host said that Biden was accepting a smaller footprint by not engaging in high-risk campaign acitivities

value.title: Trump administration removes gray wolf from endangered species list
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is dropping the gray wolf from the endangered species list under the assertion that the animal's population has sufficiently recovered, a move conservation groups decry as shortsighted and promise to challenge in court.

value.title: Biden, Cunningham hold narrow leads in North Carolina: poll
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden has a narrow lead over President Trump in North Carolina, while Democrat Cal Cunningham holds a similarly slim lead in the Tarheel State’s marquee Senate race in a new survey released Thursday.

value.title: Trump Warns ‘Bad Things’ Will Happen To ‘Treasonous’ Ex-Official Miles Taylor
value.excerpt: After calling for Taylor to be prosecuted for an anonymous 2018 op-ed, Trump extended his call to the New York Times for publishing it.

value.title: Pence stumps for vulnerable GOP senators resisting Democrat takeover
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is campaigning with four GOP senators this week in an effort to boost their precarious standing in races that will help determine which party controls the upper chamber of Congress.

value.title: Biden and Cunningham Hold Slim Leads in North Carolina, Poll Finds
value.excerpt: Joe Biden and Cal Cunningham both led their Republican rivals by three points, a Times/Siena College survey found. Perhaps most notably, 64 percent of respondents said they had already voted.

value.title: WATCH: Joe Biden holds drive-in rally in Tampa, Florida
value.excerpt: Both nominees are now focusing on encouraging voters to turn out in person on Election Day, next Tuesday. More than 73 million Americans have already voted, either by absentee or by mail.

value.title: Biden dismisses record economic growth as not 'nearly enough' to dig out of 'deep' recession
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden dismissed the U.S. economy's record-shattering growth as not "nearly enough" to get the country out of a "deep hole" on Thursday.

value.title: Former Democrat Rubin on why he is voting for Trump: 'No feeling of patriotism' on the left anymore
value.excerpt: President Trump is the last bastion to stopping the radical left, talk show host Dave Rubin said Thursday.
